                    <span>I read this book about 2 years ago to teach myself VB6. A friend of mine recently asked me to recommend a book for him to learn basic object-oriented programming on windows and this book is the only one I can think of. The book is very clearly written as is any programming book published by Wrox. Nowadays, VB.net is much more popular. I guess if you want to learn VB, buy a book on VB.net instead.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">OKAY only for beginners!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>2</span>
